  "prompt": "How do I capture raw images from an Android camera?",
  "response": "Capturing raw images from an Android camera typically involves using the Android Camera2 API, which provides comprehensive support for capturing image data in raw formats (such as YUV, RAW_SENSOR, etc.). Here\u2019s a basic overview of how to capture raw images using Android's Camera2 API.\n\n### Prerequisites\n1. **Android Studio** installed on your computer.\n2. **Android Device** that supports camera2 API and RAW image capture.\n3. **Permissions** are set in the `AndroidManifest.xml` file to access the camera and storage.\n\n### Step-by-Step Guide\n\n1. **Add Permissions in the Manifest:**\n\n   In your `AndroidManifest.xml`, make sure you have the following permissions:\n\n   ```xml\n   <uses-permission android:name=\"android.permission.CAMERA\" />\n   <uses-permission android:name=\"android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE\" />\n   <uses-feature android:name=\"android.hardware.camera\" />\n   <uses-feature android:name=\"android.hardware.camera.autofocus\" />\n   ```\n\n2. **Check for RAW Capability:**\n\n   Before capturing raw images, check if the device supports it. Use the `CameraCharacteristics` class to verify the capability.\n\n   ```java\n   CameraManager manager = (CameraManager) getSystemService(Context.CAMERA_SERVICE);\n   String cameraId = manager.getCameraIdList()[0]; // Assume using the first camera\n   CameraCharacteristics characteristics = manager.getCameraCharacteristics(cameraId);\n   int[] availableFormats = characteristics.get(CameraCharacteristics.SCALER_AVAILABLE_FORMATS);\n   boolean supportsRaw = false;\n\n   for(int format : availableFormats) {\n       if(format == ImageFormat.DNG) {\n           supportsRaw = true;\n           break;\n       }\n   }\n   ```\n\n3. **Set Up Camera Capture:**\n\n   You need to set up camera capture sessions. Use a `CameraCaptureSession` and a `CaptureRequest.Builder` configured for RAW image capture.\n\n   ```java\n   CameraCaptureSession.StateCallback stateCallback = new CameraCaptureSession.StateCallback() {\n       @Override\n       public void onConfigured(CameraCaptureSession session) {\n           try {\n               CaptureRequest.Builder captureBuilder = session.getDevice().createCaptureRequest(CameraDevice.TEMPLATE_STILL_CAPTURE);\n               captureBuilder.addTarget(imageReader.getSurface());\n               // Set the output format to RAW\n               captureBuilder.set(CaptureRequest.CONTROL_AE_MODE, CaptureRequest.CONTROL_AE_MODE_ON);\n\n               session.capture(captureBuilder.build(), new CameraCaptureSession.CaptureCallback() {\n                   @Override\n                   public void onCaptureCompleted(CameraCaptureSession session, CaptureRequest request, TotalCaptureResult result) {\n                       super.onCaptureCompleted(session, request, result);\n                       // Handle capturing of raw image (see imageReader below)\n                   }\n               }, null);\n           } catch (CameraAccessException e) {\n               e.printStackTrace();\n           }    \n       }\n\n       @Override\n       public void onError(CameraCaptureSession session, int error) {\n           // Handle the error\n       }\n   };\n   ```\n\n4. **Create ImageReader Object:**\n\n   Set up an `ImageReader` that can handle the RAW image format.\n\n   ```java\n   int width = 1920; // Set your desired width\n   int height = 1080; // Set your desired height\n   ImageReader imageReader = ImageReader.newInstance(width, height, ImageFormat.RAW_SENSOR, 2);\n   imageReader.setOnImageAvailableListener(new ImageReader.OnImageAvailableListener() {\n       @Override\n       public void onImageAvailable(ImageReader reader) {\n           Image image = reader.acquireLatestImage();\n           if (image != null) {\n               // Handle the raw image data\n               // Save the image or process as needed\n               image.close();\n           }\n       }\n   }, handler);\n   ```\n\n5. **Start Camera Preview:**\n\n   Before capturing images, start the camera preview which is useful if you want to display what the camera sees.\n\n   ```java\n   // Start camera preview logic here using TextureView or SurfaceView\n   ```\n\n6. **Capture the Image:**\n\n   To capture an image, simply trigger the `CameraCaptureSession` to take a still shot utilizing the callback defined above.\n\n### Additional Resources\n- **Android Developer Documentation**: The complete guide to `Camera2` API can be found in the Android developer documentation.\n- **Sample Projects**: You can also find Android sample projects that demonstrate camera functionality which may include capturing raw images.\n\n### Note\n- Always handle runtime permissions for camera and storage access. Users must grant these permissions for successful capture.\n- The actual implementation may differ based on your application's specific needs, including handling camera lifecycle events properly.\n\nThis is a basic overview, and for a detailed application, additional error handling, threading, and lifecycle management (such as opening and closing the camera) would be necessary.",
